      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know a helpline can help, but it feels so... superficial. like, they give you these little scripts and tell you it gets better, but nothing actually changes. the money is gone, the research is a dead end, and everyone expects me to just \"pivot\" or \"resilience\" my way out of this. but i'm just empty. there's no \"getting better\" when the thing that made my life worth living is just dead. i just feel like i'm dragging this heavy weight around every single day and i'm so sick of the struggle.",
